    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-23T02:49:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-23T02:49:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D 413:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, United Nations Command (<persName
                            corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="from">Clark</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-23T16:49:00+09:00"
                            >February 23, 1953—4:49 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C 61314. Subj is Interim Report Current Status <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> Financial Negot.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>On 21 Feb Pres <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> accepted
                        proposed <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> note drafted along lines
                        previous msgs. Agmt apparently reached settlement $82,800,000 for United
                        States oblig prior to 16 Dec 52. This figure rep compromise to our initial
                        offer of $79,739,187.88. <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> directed
                            <persName corresp="#p_PTC1">Paik</persName> verbally in presence my rep
                        to accept <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> proposal. Conversations with
                            <persName corresp="#p_PTC1">Paik</persName> on 22 Feb proceeded satis.
                        Believe solution can be reached on escalator clause. No apparent objection
                        use of Pusan wholesale price index to determine initial mil conversion rate
                        and for subsequent periodic adjustments; initial rate calculation will be
                        keyed to Pusan wholesale price index-mil conversion rate relationship of Apr
                        51. Ques of drawings heretofore made subsequent to 16 Dec unsettled at this
                        point in negot.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTC1">Paik</persName> proposed that formal agmt be
                        signed 25 Feb. <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> proposes to make the 25
                        Feb agmt effective 26 Feb in order to convenience our funding and finance
                        people by avoiding a split day.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>New subj: Indications <persName corresp="#p_PTC1">Paik</persName> will
                        present draft of new law to assembly near future for rationing of
                        essentials. Apparently <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Govt gaining
                        confidence.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Further info of significance will be forwarded as avail.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
